---
description: Prefer fail-visible behavior over stale or silent data fallbacks
alwaysApply: true
---

# Fail visibly — never paper over bad data

This app supports trading decisions. Prefer a hard failure or an explicit unavailable/error state over fallbacks that could show stale, approximate, or silently degraded numbers.

Never serve expired cache after a failed fetch, chain alternate endpoints just to hide errors, or substitute a related field for a missing intended value unless the product explicitly documents that substitution.

When required market data cannot be loaded: throw or return a clear error, surface it in the UI, and keep in-TTL cache for performance only — not as silent recovery.
